alley Girl Speak” is High Rising Terminal. Surprisingly, this is a phenomenon that has been studied in England, Australia, and New Zealand. Some linguistics believe it originated in the 1950s and others believe it’s centuries old (aka older than the 1980s Valley Girl caricature). Even though “Valley Girl Speak” is almost exclusively used to describe women, men use rising intonation as well. While making simple declarative statements, men and women were found to use rising-intonation similarly. %0a%3c %0a%3c Sources: %0a%3c %0a%3c https://www.wm.edu/as/sociology/news-events/news-archive/2013-14-archive/overturning.the.myth.of.valley.girl.speack.php%0a%3c https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valley_girl%0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c %0a%3c [[#contentends]]%0a%3c ----%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
